The paper deals with the problem of identifying phishing attacks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves using machine learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks (RNNs), to classify phishing content. This falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the textual structure of emails, which suggests that it could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of RNNs for classification could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), although this is less likely given the focus on emails in this paper.
